{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:50:03.060Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"a1maushb","input":{"summary":"### Summary of Implementation\nWe have completely redesigned and elevated the OREMesh, RetailMesh, and TelecomVerse platform pages into premium, high-fidelity enterprise interfaces that look custom-built by a senior designer and implemented by a senior frontend engineer.\n\n1. **OREMesh Edge Platform (`app/platforms/oremesh/page.tsx`)**:\n   - **Strategic Resilient Statement**: Highlighting ruggedized edge operations.\n   - **Interactive Subterranean Node Blueprint**: A bespoke interactive SVG diagram showing deep mine shaft faces, transport fleets, and satellite uplinks that update an inspector panel on-click.\n   - **Autonomy & Backhaul Simulator**: A fully interactive terminal console enabling users to toggle satellite link connectivity. It showcases real-time offline buffering, differential syncing, cryptographic local signing, and 12ms local dispatch alerts under disconnected states.\n   - **Resilient Modules Carousel & Bento Grid**: Mapping out AES-256 keys, differential bandwidth ratios, and low-latency metrics.\n\n2. **RetailMesh Platform (`app/platforms/retailmesh/page.tsx`)**:\n   - **Strategic Omnichannel Statement**: Focused on secure, decoupled checkout visibility.\n   - **Storefront-to-Cloud Distributed Blueprint**: An interactive SVG topology connecting checkouts, storefront servers, and the sovereign cloud.\n   - **PII Masking & Sync Simulator**: An interactive payment input form coupled with a GFF PII Masking Shield toggle. Processing a transaction demonstrates real-time masking (e.g., Charlotte Dubois -> C********* D******) and tokenization on the edge before syncing.\n   - **Platform Carousel & Bento Grid**: Showcasing PCI-DSS compliance, 99.99% storefront uptime, and vector search speeds.\n\n3. **TelecomVerse Core (`app/platforms/telecomverse/page.tsx`)**:\n   - **Strategic Carrier Statement**: Resilient DWDM backbone and fiber routing.\n   - **Carrier Telemetry Topology Blueprint**: An interactive SVG network backhaul grid connecting cell towers, microwave bases, and optical cores.\n   - **Carrier Load & Resiliency Simulator**: Enables users to simulate a physical fiber cut to watch GFF routing agents automatically reroute packets via UHF Microwave in 12 microseconds, registering 0 packet drops. Includes simulated telemetry log ingestion (up to 1.85M logs/sec) and automated field dispatcher ticket generation.\n   - **Platform Carousel & Bento Grid**: Detailing sovereign tunnels, sub-microsecond rerouting failovers, and eBPF kernel logging.\n\n---\n### Validation Done\n- **Mobile Responsiveness**: Ensured responsive grid layout (`grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12`) and flex alignment (`flex-col md:flex-row`) for perfect display on both narrow mobile screens and large ultra-wide monitors.\n- **Accessibility & Contrast**: Built high-contrast controls, logical semantic elements, accessible heading structures, and explicit hover/focus micro-interactions.\n- **Production Verification**: Executed a full Next.js production build (`npm run build`) which succeeded perfectly with absolutely zero TypeScript compiler errors or linter warnings.\n\n---\n### Limitations\n- Simulator interactions and state updates are processed via fully front-end-only placeholder states (client-side React hooks) as required by GFF AI backend-free project guardrails.","verified":true}}}
